# Contributing

Thanks for your interest in contributing to `{{ package_name }}`.

## Setup

Fork the project on GitLab, then clone your fork:

```shell
git clone git@gitlab.com:{{ package_gitlab_namespace }}/{{ package_name }}.git
cd {{ package_name }}
```

Install the development environment:

```shell
uv sync --all-extras
uv run pre-commit install
```

## Development Workflow

Run linting and tests before opening a merge request:

```shell
make lint
make test
```

You can also run pre-commit directly:

```shell
uv run pre-commit run --all-files
```

## Merge Requests

Create a feature branch, push it to GitLab, and open a merge request:

```shell
git checkout -b my-change
git push -u origin my-change
```

Keep merge requests focused and include tests for behavior changes.
